snippet.title: Shaky ( Official #Video ) Sanju Rathod Ft. Isha Malviya | G-Spark | New #Marathi Songs 2025
snippet.description:
Provided To Youtube By Amal Star Media
| üïâ ||
Sanju Rathod presents 'Shaky' a Marathi track like no other!

Shaky is a fresh Marathi Pop anthem that blends playful Afrobeat grooves with everyday desi charm. Sanju Rathod and Isha Malviya bring effortless swag, catchy hooks, and vibrant energy in this fun, feel-good love track. A bold, danceable vibe that pushes Marathi music into exciting new territory.

Singer - Sanju Rathod
LyricsComposer - Sanju Rathod
Music Produced By - G-Spark
Vocal Production Mixed By - G-Spark
Additional Mix Mastered By - Rupendar Venkatesh @mixmagic Studios
Recorded By - Jagdish Bhandge @Apostrophe Studios

snippet.description:
üî• The Wait Is Over! FFMAI 2025 BR Play-Ins Day 1 is HERE! üî•

After months of anticipation, the moment has finally arrived! The Free Fire MAX Asia Invitational 2025 kicks off today with the Battle Royale Play-Ins!

This is where the road to the Main Event begins:

18 invited teams have entered the Play-Ins, but only the Top 10 will survive to advance and join the 8 Seeded Teams in the Main Event. The competition is cutthroat‚Äîevery point matters, and there is no room for error.

Today, Group B faces off against Group C. These squads are fighting not just for a Booyah, but for their survival in the tournament.

Playing Today:
Group B: Reflex United, Nightmare Esports, Rising Gods, Kagendra, Red Cliff, Head Hunters. 
Group C: Avida x KDC, GB Esports, Meta Ninza, Revenant Xspark, Fangs, iQOO Reckoning.

The cheers will roar, the pressure is real, and the race for the Top 10 starts today.

18 Teams. 10 Qualifying Spots. The fight for survival begins NOW! üëë

snippet.title: Mowgli Trailer | Roshan Kanakala | Bandi Saroj Kumar | Sandeep Raj | Sakkshi | TG Vishwa Prasad
snippet.description:
Mowgli 2025 will arrive in cinemas on December 12th, 2025.

Mowgli is an upcoming 2025 unique romantic action drama set deep within a forest backdrop. Directed by National Award-winning filmmaker Sandeep Raj (Colour Photo), Produced by TG Vishwa Prasad and Krithi Prasad under People Media Factory Banner.The film has cinematography by Rama Maruthi M, while Kaala Bhairava scores the music. The work is co-written by Rama Maruthi M and Radhakrishna Reddy The technical team also includes Peekay as editor, Kiran Mamidi as art director, and Natraj Madigonda choreographing the action sequences.

snippet.title: Case - Official Video | Chandra Brar FT Deepak Dhillon | Gaiphy | New Punjabi song
snippet.description:
Chandra Brar presents ‚ÄòCase‚Äô ‚Äì "Gagsta Soul, Goofy Hard"

Song- Case
Singer- Chandra Brar feat Deepak Dhillon
Female Lead- Samridhi Puri
Lyrics & Composer- Chandra Brar
Music- Gaiphy
Mix/Master- Sameer Charegaonkar
DOP- Harry Saini
Edit- Bhullar Editing Studio
Poster- MG Visuals
Female Costumes- Label Parul Prabhakar

Directed by The Mohit Bawa

Associate Director- Vansh Gumti
Directions Team - Arvi Sandhu, Maan Singh
Making- Ritik Kataria
Line Producer- Amandeep Singh, Davinder Singh
Co Artists- Gurshaan, Sekhon Noorpuri, Tejpal, Baaz, Gur Mand, Harjeet Dhaliwal, Davinder Singh, Param Kanda, Sharry Kanda, Akash Maur, Komal Bhullar, Harjot, 
Project by- Adab Entertainment, Karanvirr
Produced by- Buta Brar
Online Promotion- Vibeline Media
Special Thanks -D.P Transport , Oxbridge School, Rishi School, Sidhu Tailor, Jaspal Sekhon nd Kotapura Police nd Kotkapura citizens 

Song Lyrics:

Kehda bolu vehm jya kadd de
Hun darna durna shad de,
Tu hath jihda ae fadya ohda hath cop na fad de,
Independent artist te teri mukhtyari ni,
Fukri fakri marya kar teri Jatt nale sabji bna yari ni,
Fukri vadu marya Kar ter Jatt nal yaari ni

Ki Shakya lal ter akh ve
Kahdi lad di a tenu makh ve,
Kahnu dab vich tangi firda tera lag jana ae lakh ve,
Kehdi gall to tidya firda ae das yara ve,
Koi Case pawake bethenga lagdai Dildara ve,
Dhara lagwa k bethenga lagdai Dildara ve

Teri age kude a eni mere nal jine a rehnde,
Sada vairi na koi band da asi aap ja k aan khehnde,
Ohda na koi ilaj kre jihde satt mari ni,
Hye Fukri fakri marya kar ter jatt nal yari ni

Hadd tutt jane jiwe taare
Ve tenu honi vaajan maare,
Kal opre chehre sunya puchde collage tere bare,
Utto sunya main policia da hath hunda bhara ve,
Koi Case pawake bethenga lagdai Dildara ve

Tu pawe soota te booti ni jatt balliye gema paunda,
Tera yaar choti da rader a inj balliye hath ni aunda,
Goli wangu sun jandi thapi patt mari ni,
Fukri fakri marya Kar teri jatt nal yaari ni

Ki favourite ae rang thoda ghumde o ehde daale,
Asla feem te rehnde khunde Sadhan rakh lye kale,
Main sunya utto velly ne ve tere Kotkapure wale,
Kyo naam varge kam krda ae Chandre Brara ve,
Koi Case pawake bethenga lagdai Dildara ve

On the auspicious occasion of Shri Datta Jayanti, we present the soulful and divine Dattatreya Aarti, sung by the melodious Prathamesh Laghate, only on Tips Bhakti Prem.
 Immerse yourself in devotion as this powerful Marathi Aarti praises Lord Dattatreya, the divine embodiment of Brahma, Vishnu, and Mahesh.

About Lord Dattatreya
Lord Dattatreya is revered as the combined incarnation of Brahma, Vishnu, and Mahesh, symbolizing creation, preservation, and dissolution. Considered the Adi Guru (the original spiritual master), he embodies ultimate knowledge, detachment, and inner freedom.
 Devotees believe that worshipping Lord Datta removes fears, resolves karmic obstacles, guides the seeker on the path of truth, and grants protection and blessings.

About Datta Jayanti
Datta Jayanti marks the divine birth of Lord Dattatreya and is celebrated with deep devotion. On this day, devotees chant Datta Stotras, read Guru Charitra, perform prayers, and seek spiritual guidance from the Lord of the Three Worlds.
Immerse yourself in this powerful aarti and invoke the blessings of Shri Gurudatta.

To receive regular updates on devotional songs subscribe to us on the following link: https://www.youtube.com/BhaktiPrem

On the auspicious occasion of Shri Datta Jayanti, we present the soulful and divine Dattatreya Aarti, sung by the melodious Prathamesh Laghate, only on Tips Bhakti Prem.
 Immerse yourself in devotion as this powerful Marathi Aarti praises Lord Dattatreya, the divine embodiment of Brahma, Vishnu, and Mahesh.

About Lord Dattatreya
Lord Dattatreya is revered as the combined incarnation of Brahma, Vishnu, and Mahesh, symbolizing creation, preservation, and dissolution. Considered the Adi Guru (the original spiritual master), he embodies ultimate knowledge, detachment, and inner freedom.
 Devotees believe that worshipping Lord Datta removes fears, resolves karmic obstacles, guides the seeker on the path of truth, and grants protection and blessings.

About Datta Jayanti
Datta Jayanti marks the divine birth of Lord Dattatreya and is celebrated with deep devotion. On this day, devotees chant Datta Stotras, read Guru Charitra, perform prayers, and seek spiritual guidance from the Lord of the Three Worlds.
Immerse yourself in this powerful aarti and invoke the blessings of Shri Gurudatta.

To receive regular updates on devotional songs subscribe to us on the following link: https://www.youtube.com/BhaktiPrem

On the auspicious occasion of Shri Datta Jayanti, we present the soulful and divine Dattatreya Aarti, sung by the melodious Prathamesh Laghate, only on Tips Bhakti Prem.
 Immerse yourself in devotion as this powerful Marathi Aarti praises Lord Dattatreya, the divine embodiment of Brahma, Vishnu, and Mahesh.

About Lord Dattatreya
Lord Dattatreya is revered as the combined incarnation of Brahma, Vishnu, and Mahesh, symbolizing creation, preservation, and dissolution. Considered the Adi Guru (the original spiritual master), he embodies ultimate knowledge, detachment, and inner freedom.
 Devotees believe that worshipping Lord Datta removes fears, resolves karmic obstacles, guides the seeker on the path of truth, and grants protection and blessings.

About Datta Jayanti
Datta Jayanti marks the divine birth of Lord Dattatreya and is celebrated with deep devotion. On this day, devotees chant Datta Stotras, read Guru Charitra, perform prayers, and seek spiritual guidance from the Lord of the Three Worlds.
Immerse yourself in this powerful aarti and invoke the blessings of Shri Gurudatta.

To receive regular updates on devotional songs subscribe to us on the following link: https://www.youtube.com/BhaktiPrem
